HEADWORD: Seaweed
<hw>Sea"weed`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Popularly, any plant or plants growing in the sea.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Any marine plant of the class
Algae, as kelp, dulse, <gen>Fucus</gen>, <gen>Ulva</gen>, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sea whip</ent>⟦br⟧
